The '''Esfandia Long-Range Communications Base''' was a mobile base on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Esfandia/Legends|Esfandia]].

The base was built on existing [[All Terrain Armored Transport/Legends|AT-AT]] technology, allowing it to move slowly but steadily around the planet, maintaining and repairing the limited communications relays between the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]] and the known [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxy]]. The base was built with narrow but tall corridors and contained an extravehicular bay with five [[Speeder bike/Legends|speeder bikes]] and [[Environment suit/Legends|enviro-suits]] for additional outside repairs.

During the [[Battle of Esfandia]], thirteen of the original forty communications relays on the planet were destroyed as a result of Yuuzhan Vong bombardment, cutting close to [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Ashpidar]]'s fifty-percent safety margin. The crew of the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] stumbled upon the base and helped the crew escape destruction at the hands of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] and the traitor in their midst. Security chief [[Eniknar]] sacrificed himself to save the remaining crew from the Yuuzhan Vong, setting off a series of bombs.

